and current status of Nikkei society in a given country? Are there any common attributes the Nikkei share across the Americas, especially in terms of social institutions, the family, the position of women, religion, education, politics, and economics? What are the significant differences between the Nikkei populations in the various countries and why have these differences developed? What are the future prospects of Nikkei communities in the Americas?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aAmemiya, Kozy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArakaki, Makoto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAraki, Raljl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAzuma, Eiichiro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBefu, Harumi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHiga, Marcelo G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHirabayashi, James A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHirabayashi, James A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHirabayashi, Lane Ryo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHirabayashi, Lane Ryo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHoki Moniz, Naomi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIino, Masako, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aInui, Lloyd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKasama Tsu, Emi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKikumura-Yano, Akemi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKikumura-Yano, Akemi, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc